:: BUY {"position":"500,500","size":"100,100"}
At the corner shop, two things catch your attention:
- A sturdy umbrella for **$15**
- A cheap but filling meal for **$10**

You can’t afford both.

What do you buy?

[[Buy the umbrella->BUY UMBRELLA]]
[[Buy the food->BUY FOOD]]
[[Buy nothing and save the money->BUY NOTHING]]


:: BUY FOOD {"position":"700,500","size":"100,100"}
(set: $ateFood to true)
(set: $money to $money - 10)

You eat quickly under the store’s awning.

You feel calmer. A little stronger.

[[Go home->GO HOME]]


:: BUY NOTHING {"position":"700,700","size":"100,100"}
You decide to save the money.
Your hunger doesn’t agree with that decision.

[[Go home->GO HOME]]


:: BUY UMBRELLA {"position":"700,300","size":"100,100"}
(set: $hasUmbrella to true)
(set: $money to $money - 15)

You buy the umbrella. The rain drums loudly against it as you walk.
At least you’ll stay dry.

[[Go home->GO HOME]]


